==English==

===Etymology===
Aphetic for obsolete ''[[evanish]]'', Old French ''[[esvanir]], [[esvaniss-]]'' (French ''[[évanouir]]''), Vular Latin ''[[evanescere]]'', from ''[[vanus]]'', "empty".

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: văn'ĭsh
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /ˈvænɪʃ/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /"v@nIS/

===Verb===
{{en-verb|vanish|vanishes|vanished|vanishing}}
# To become [[invisible]] or move out of [[view]] [[unnoticed]].
# (''Mathematics'') To become [[equal]] to [[zero]].
#:''The function f(x)=x^2 '''vanishes''' at x=0.''

====Synonyms====
*[[disappear]]

